name: Paul Auster
summary: Renowned author Paul Auster, best known for his "City of Glass" novel and "The New York Trilogy," has passed away at the age of 77. His innovative and experimental writing style, spanning novels, screenplays, and films, made him a significant figure in contemporary literature. His "New York Trilogy," in particular, gained him international recognition, establishing him as a postmodern master. Auster's prolific body of work left an enduring mark on the literary world, garnering him critical acclaim and a wide readership.
